        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<div class="admonition tip"><p class="admonition-title"><span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span> Tip</p><p>PhpStorm has a great refactoring tool to rename everything automatically. Check out
the <a href="../phpstorm/refactoring">Refactoring in PhpStorm</a> tutorial.</p>
</div><h2 id="adding-the-join">Adding the Join <a class="headerlink" href="query-with-join#adding-the-join" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Let's go to work! Remove the <code>orderBy</code> line. We need to order by the <code>createdAt</code>
field in the <code>genus_note</code> table. And we know from SQL that we can't do that unless
we <em>join</em> over to that table. Do that with, <code>-&gt;leftJoin('genus')</code> - because that's
the alias we set on line 15 - <code>genus.notes</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="c066649201">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
