</div>
</p>
<p>Why <code>notes</code>? This is the <em>property</em> name on <code>Genus</code> that references the relationship.
And just by mentioning it, Doctrine has all the info it needs to generate the full JOIN SQL.</p>
<h2 id="joins-and-the-inverse-relation">Joins and the Inverse Relation <a class="headerlink" href="query-with-join#joins-and-the-inverse-relation" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Remember, this is the optional, <em>inverse</em> side of the relationship: we added this
for the convenience of being able to say <code>$genus-&gt;getNotes()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="3e7a65447d">
