	                                <p>Hey Maksym,</p><p>MySQL returns denormalized data as any SQL server when you use JOIN operations, that's why Doctrine normalizes this data for you. Doctrine knows that you query data FROM *genus* table, so it returns unique objects from it (actually, it hydrates objects based on denormalized data set). So all this magic handles by ORM itself.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
