	            	                <li class="dsq-comment dsq-clearfix" data-dsq-comment-id="2640338885" id="dsq-comment-2640338885">
	                    <div class="dsq-avatar dsq-tt">
	                        <a href="https://disqus.com/by/weaverryan/">
	                            	                                <img alt="" src="http://a.disquscdn.com/uploads/users/32/6480/avatar92.jpg?1482356913">
	                            	                        </a>
	                    </div>
	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-2640338885">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-04-24</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">weaverryan</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2640338885" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2640338885" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Roy!</p><p>This is basically a "Method not found" error - the EntityRepository has a magic __call method that makes this method look different :). Three things to check:</p><p>1) Double-check that you don't have any typos on the name in either GenusRepository or GenusController (you probably don't, as you mentioned you changed it in both spots - but just in case)</p><p>2) Make sure that you're asking for -&gt;getRepository('AppBundle:Genus') - make sure you're not asking for some other class's repository.</p><p>3) Make sure that when you ask for -&gt;getRepository('AppBundle:Genus'), you're getting back an instance of `GenusRepository`. As long as you have the property repositoryClass configuration above Genus, you should. But to be sure, you can do this:</p><p><code><pre>dump($this-&gt;getDoctrine()-&gt;getManager()-&gt;getRepository('AppBundle:Genus'));die;<br></pre></code></p><p>I hope one of these things helps!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
